div.p:
The Civilians, who are not in all points so great friends to Monarchy as the Common-Law of England, do allow Six Regalia's to a Supreme Magistrate:

 VIZ.

                  1. Armamenta;

All kind of Arming;
                  2. Potestas Judicatoria;

Power of Judicature;
                  3. Potestas Vitae & Necis;

Power of Life and Death;
                  4. Bona Adespota;

Masterless Goods;
                  5 Census;

Sessements and Publick Taxations.
                  6. Monetarum valor;

The value, and coyning of Money.
